enigma_edit.lua

Interface Constants

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Constants.BottleState, Constants.CoinState, Constants.ColorState, Constants.Controllers, Constants.CrackState, Constants.DiscoState, Constants.DoorState, Constants.Essential, Constants.ExtinguisherState, Constants.FloodState, Constants.GlassesState, Constants.MeditationState, Constants.Orientation, Constants.OxydColor, Constants.OxydState, Constants.QuakeState, Constants.RotatorState, Constants.State, Constants.SubSoil, Constants.SwitchState, Constants.YinYangState

    public interface Constants
    A base interface for all constants, the Enigma API defines. This is just a convenience type, grouping all enums, that represent such constants into one super-type and providing some functions dealing with these constants (code data initialization and integer-to-constant conversion).

      • initialize

        static void initialize(CodeData data)
        Add instances of all constants to the given data structure. Each constant defined within this interface and its nested classes, will be added to the given CodeData instance as objects of ConstValue.
        Parameters:
        data - The target data structure.

      • isCheckedKind

        static boolean isCheckedKind(java.lang.String kind)
        Check, if the given kind has attributes, whose values are expected to be predefined constants. This is called by checkConst(java.lang.String, java.lang.String, int) to abort checking without gathering all the data, if the checked tile does not have any attributes worth checking.
        Parameters:
        kind - Kind to check.
        Returns:
        true, if this kind has attributes, which should make use of predefined constants.

      • isCheckedAttribute

        static boolean isCheckedAttribute(java.lang.String attribute)
        Check, if the given attribute prefers predefined constants as its values. This is called by checkConst(java.lang.String, java.lang.String, int) to abort checking without gathering all the data, if the checked tile does not have any attributes worth checking.
        Parameters:
        attribute - Attribute to check.
        Returns:
        true, if this attribute might have special constant values.

      • checkConst

        static Constants checkConst(java.lang.String kind,
                            java.lang.String attribute,
                            int value)
        Check, if the given value can be represented by a predefined constant. This check needs the object kind and the attribute name, to determine, which set of constants to use.
        Parameters:
        kind - Enigma object kind hosting the attribute.
        attribute - Attribute name.
        value - Numeric value of the attribute.
        Returns:
        A value of a Constants enum-type, or null, if the attribute does not use constants.

      • checkTable

        static void checkTable(Table val)
        Check a tile's attributes for integer literals, that can be converted to constants. If the given table represents a tile, its attributes are checked by checkConst(java.lang.String, java.lang.String, int) and possibly converted to the given constant.
        Parameters:
        val - A table, that defines a tile (or a part thereof).
